CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, p. 1, reads: "Landslide Imperils Street - The bonding company for the Belmar Gardens Cooperative Housing Association already has a construction company working on a phase of the $67,000 project to prevent further sliding of this area of Belmar Gardens. Tons of rain-loosened earth, in a year's period, have eased down the hillside to inundate part of Apple St. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Men and children standing on top of hill with landslide, fallen chain link fence in foreground, and Belmar Gardens buildings in background, Homewood
